<item>
            <title>[LU-13094] Handle ENOENT lookup failure correctly on MDT</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13094</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In current Lustre code, lookup() or getattr() via IT_LOOKUP or IT_GETATTR in mdt_intent_getattr will treat -ENOENT error wrongly as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        rc = mdt_getattr_name_lock(info, lhc, child_bits, ldlm_rep);
	ldlm_rep-&amp;gt;lock_policy_res2 = clear_serious(rc);

        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (mdt_get_disposition(ldlm_rep, DISP_LOOKUP_NEG))
                ldlm_rep-&amp;gt;lock_policy_res2 = 0;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When DISP_LOOKUP_NEG is set, we can not set the status of intent lock with 0. Otherwise, the client will cache and validate the dentry incorrectly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
